news.title: Shimao-guaranteed $174 million notes due March may not be redeemed - trustee
news.para: Regulatory curbs on borrowing have driven China's property sector into a liquidity crisis, with the struggles of Evergrande , the world's most indebted property firm, to repay its borrowings mirrored at several smaller rivals.

news.title: Max Estates lease out 1.05 lakh sq ft space in Delhi at around Rs 16 crore annual rent
news.para: "Average rental rate for Max House Phase 1 now stands at around Rs 125 per square feet per month," the statement said. Samsung India Electronics, Nykaa Fashion, Religare Enterprises, DSK Legal and Dhampur Sugar Mills are some of the key occupiers.

news.title: Tata Housing to invest $36 million to develop two residential projects in Maldives
news.para: Tata Housing, which entered the Maldives market around a decade ago, has already completed a social housing project in the island country in partnership with the Maldives government.

news.title: MoEF panel gives green nod to JSW's steel plant project
news.para: An expert appraisal committee of the Union ministry of environment and climate change (MoEF&CC) has recommended grant of environment clearance (EC) for JSW Utkal Steel Ltd’s proposed steel plant near Paradip in Jagatsinghpur district.

news.title: DDA allots 679 households to Jhuggi Jhopri dwellers of Bhumiheen Camp
news.para: "Out of 2,700 households of Bhumiheen Camp, the eligibility in respect of 679 households has been decided in respect of Jhuggi Jhopri (JJ) dwellers whose documents were found complete," the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) said in a statement.

news.title: Kanpur: House owners can file mutation applications offline also
news.para: All zonal officers and tax inspectors have been asked to deposit the mutation fee offline. They have been directed to conduct an inspection of their office once in a week and check the desk of each clerk to examine the status of pending mutation cases.

news.title: Mahagun Mantra residents seek resurfacing of 400 meter stretch of road
news.para: Rajesh Kumar, a resident of Mahagun Mantra, said, “Our society is not in a good shape. Though the builders have given possession of flats after a delay of five years, the homebuyers have no option but to shift as they are burdened with heavy EMIs.

news.title: Title change for two prime Aurangabad properties
news.para: Authorities said that recently, the Union government’s custodian of EP had held a video conference with district collectors and reviewed the status of “enemy properties”.

news.title: Ease layout formation rules, urge realtors in Krishna district
news.para: The approval of the director of town and country planning (DTCP) is mandatory for converting agricultural land into housing plots.

news.title: Lucknow development body looks for land to replicate Light House Project
news.para: According to LDA officials, the development authority has constituted a committee which will look for areas under LDA jurisdiction for the development of the Light House Project.

news.title: Gurugram civic body issues new property tax notices to owners
news.para: Of the total of 5.03 lakh properties under the tax ambit, 3.16 lakh are residential buildings, 61,571 commercial ones, 4,983 industrial units, 2,014 institutional units and 78,820 are vacant plots.

news.title: Bihar government lifts curbs on building heights in urban areas
news.para: Earlier, a maximum of 24 metres height was allowed for a building on a 40 feet wide road and 22 metres on a 30 feet wide road. Now, a G+6 building can be constructed on a 40 feet wide road and G+4 building with a maximum height of 16 metres on a 25 feet wide road.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso cave-in could have been averted if cops had acted on plaint: Residents
news.para: They alleged that they had gone to Bajghera police station seeking an FIR against the builder when a portion of a balcony collapsed six months ago, but police refused to register the case.

news.title: Delhi: 14 years on, Kathputli Colony dream closer to reality for some
news.para: A DDA official said out of 2,800 one-bedroom flats to be allotted to slum dwellers, 500 would be handed over by March 31 in apartment blocks that were complete. The remaining 2,300 flats would be allotted by the end of 2022.

news.title: Maharashtra CM inaugurates Patra chawl redevelopment project
news.para: “The tenants of Patra Chawl have moved a step towards getting their homes. I give my word that they will get their homes in the next three years,” said Awhad.
